@page "/openai-instructions"

<MudPaper>
    <MudCardContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Instructions to create an OpenAI API key:</MudText>
        <MudList>
            <MudListItem>1. Visit the OpenAI website at https://www.openai.com/ </MudListItem>
            <MudListItem>2. Click on the "Sign Up" button to create a new account. </MudListItem>
            <MudListItem>3. After you've created your account and signed in, go to the OpenAI Dashboard. </MudListItem>
            <MudListItem>4. In the Dashboard, there should be a section for "API keys". Click the "Create API key" button. </MudListItem>
            <MudListItem>5. You'll need to give your new key a name and, optionally, a description. </MudListItem>
            <MudListItem>6. Make sure to record your key somewhere safe, as you'll need it to authenticate your requests to the OpenAI API. Also, be sure not to share your key, as it could be used to make requests on your behalf.</MudListItem>
        </MudList>
        <MudText>Be sure to review OpenAI's pricing and rate limit information to understand potential charges and usage constraints. For more detailed instructions, you can visit the <MudLink Href="https://beta.openai.com/docs/developer-quickstart/your-api-keys/" Target="_blank">OpenAI's guide</MudLink>.</MudText>
    </MudCardContent>
</MudPaper>